    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>A New York Walk</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steven M Clayton letter on Seth Kugel's May 27 column on architectural landmarks in New York City</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: I really enjoyed Seth Kugel's ''Architectural Landmarks: A Tour With Head Tilted Up'' (Weekend in New York, May 27), which proposed a great walking path. It is funny: I have lived in the area my entire life, yet there are parts of the city that always give me a rush of excitement, no matter how many times I've seen them. This is what makes New York the greatest city in the world; its depth and excitement can't be matched.</p>
        <p>Steven M. Clayton  Ocean, N.J.</p>
      </block>
